Olmegenyu Secondary School, Narok, trounced big names during the Mau Regional Drama Festival at Samoei Girls Secondary School in Nandi.Olmegenyu will represent the region during the national bonanza in Kisumu on April 2.The school won the Film category, a new item introduced this year, beating national schools from Bomet, Kericho and Uasin Gishu. The winning item was written and produced by Mark Anthony.Despite having limited resource for practice, the school win was remarkable. It was their first time to participate in the drama festival. Drama patron Betty Aruasa said the winning item, Feature, majored on indiscipline cases among students. The play was seen as a message to students to be disciplined, set with the background of students&rsquo; unrest in schools which led to many closures last year.